FT  28 APR 93 / International Company News: Procter ahead in third term
PROCTER &amp; GAMBLE, the large consumer products company, announced an 8.9 per
cent increase in after-tax profits for the three months to end-March, at
Dollars 516m.
P &amp; G, which has made an unchanged Dollars 1.53bn after-tax in the first
nine months, said the third-quarter increase reflected lower costs and good
volume growth.
Fully-diluted earnings per share for the quarter were 67 cents against 62
cents but sales fell by 1.8 per cent to Dollars 7.35bn.
